Sentencas: Anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) composed of NiO-SDC (Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9) composite anode, thin tri-layer electrolyte, and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3 (LSCF)-La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) composite cathode were fabricated.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of Anode-supported LaGaO3-based Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Sm-doped CeO2 Buffer Layers

Sentencas: The thin 11 mu m SDC/15 mu m LSGM/13 mu m SDC tri-layer electrolyte was prepared by centrifugal casting and co-firing technique.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of Anode-supported LaGaO3-based Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Sm-doped CeO2 Buffer Layers

Sentencas: Cell tests in air as oxidant and humidified hydrogen as fuel show a maximum power density of 0.92 W/cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of Anode-supported LaGaO3-based Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Sm-doped CeO2 Buffer Layers

Sentencas: However, the open-circuit voltage (OCV) of these cells is 0.89 V which is lower than the Nernst potential.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of Anode-supported LaGaO3-based Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Sm-doped CeO2 Buffer Layers

Sentencas: The above result is due to electronic conductivity in the LSGM layer, resulting from Ni impurities that entered during co-firing with the NiO-SDC anode.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of Anode-supported LaGaO3-based Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Sm-doped CeO2 Buffer Layers

Sentencas: While the SDC buffer layers are introduced as buffer layers, impedance measurements indicate that both the ohmic resistance and the polarization resistance dominate the cell performance.
Titulo: Preparation and Performance of Anode-supported LaGaO3-based Electrolyte Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Sm-doped CeO2 Buffer Layers
